cmquhlq1z00160rto6yoa127u	cmquhhdsp00000rtoj5chbd5s	PARAGRAPH	يوم عائلتي	Mixed (daily life, masjid, studying, family)	في كل يوم، أصحو مبكرًا لأستعد للمدرسة. أفطر مع عائلتي، وأسأل أبي كم وجبةً تأكل في اليوم؟ يقول أبي: آكل ثلاث وجبات: الفطور والغداء والعشاء. بعد الدراسة، أذهب إلى المسجد لصلاة المغرب. أحب المسجد، فأشعر بالسكينة هناك. في المنزل، أقارب دراستي مع أخي، ونتحدث عن المواد الدراسية.	فِي كُلِّ يَوْمٍ، أَصْحُو مُبَكِّرًا لأَسْتَعِدَّ لِلْمَدْرَسَةِ. أَفْطَرُ مَعَ عَائِلَتِي، وَأَسْأَلُ أَبِي كَمْ وَجْبَةً تَأكُلُ فِي اليَوْمِ؟ يَقُولُ أَبِي: آكُلُ ثَلَاثَ وَجَبَاتٍ: الفُطُورَ والغَدَاءَ والعَشَاءَ. بَعْدَ الدِّرَاسَةِ، أَذْهَبُ إِلَى الْمَسْجِدِ لِصَلَاةِ الْمَغْرِبِ. أُحِبُّ الْمَسْجِدَ، فَأَشْعُرُ بِالسَّكِينَةِ هُنَاكَ. فِي الْمَنْزِلِ، أُقَارِبُ دِرَاسَتِي مَعَ أَخِي، وَنَتَحَدَّثُ عَنِ الْمَوَادِّ الدِّرَاسِيَّةِ.	\N	Every day, I wake up early to get ready for school. I eat breakfast with my family, and I ask my dad how many meals he eats in a day? My father says: "I eat three meals: breakfast, lunch, and dinner." After the lesson, I go to the masjid for Maghrib prayer. I love the masjid, since I feel at peace there. In the (i don't know), I go over my lessons with my brother, and we talk about the class schedule.	{"score":85,"summary":"The translation is mostly accurate, but there are a few mistakes and misunderstandings regarding vocabulary and structure.","fullTranslation":"Every day, I wake up early to get ready for school. I eat breakfast with my family, and I ask my dad how many meals he eats in a day. My father says: 'I eat three meals: breakfast, lunch, and dinner.' After school, I go to the mosque for Maghrib prayer. I love the mosque, as I feel at peace there. At home, I study with my brother, and we talk about the subjects.","corrections":[{"original":"After the lesson","correction":"After school","why":"The term 'lesson' does not accurately reflect the context of school."},{"original":"masjid","correction":"mosque","why":"The term 'masjid' is less common in English; 'mosque' is preferred."},{"original":"I go over my lessons","correction":"I study","why":"The phrase 'go over my lessons' is less natural than 'study'."},{"original":"class schedule","correction":"subjects","why":"The original Arabic refers to 'subjects' rather than 'class schedule'."}],"grammarNotes":["The use of 'how many meals he eats in a day?' should be a statement, not a question.","The phrase 'I love the masjid, since I feel at peace there' is better as 'as' instead of 'since'."],"missedWords":[{"arabic":"مَنْزِلِ","english":"home","type":"noun","root":"ن ز ل","past":"نَزَلَ","present":"يَنْزِلُ","masdar":"نُزُول","imperative":"اِنزِلْ","example":"أَنا أَعيشُ في المَنْزِلِ.","exampleEnglish":"I live in the home."}],"wordResults":[],"aiWordResults":[{"arabic":"المَسْجِدِ","english":"mosque","outcome":"missed"}],"source":"ai"}	85	{"usedWordIds":[],"offered":2,"source":"ai"}	{"ratio":{"mastered":70,"review":20,"new":10},"difficulty":"MEDIUM","harakatMode":"FULL","paragraphLength":"MEDIUM","aiVocabMode":"NORMAL"}	t	2026-06-26 05:25:03.143	2026-06-26 05:30:04.122
